Amy Hughes ran 53 marathons in 53 days to raise money for a friend’s daughter who was diagnosed with a brain tumour . 
  The sports therapist smashed the world record and raised £30,000 for charity . 
  She ran 1,388 miles and went through five different pairs of trainers . 
  She also got close to long-term friend Dave Keighley who was part of her support crew . 
 